# ===========================================================================
%NAME Samples2, Suite 1: addresses superset test
# ===========================================================================
%DESCRIPTION
# ??????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????
Query the "sakila_adress" view in VDP, which is a base view with data
coming directly from the "sakila" data source, and compare it with the
"all_addresses" union view also in VDP, which should contain a SUPERSET of
the addresses in the former source.
# ===========================================================================
%EXECUTION[query]
{ ds:vdp }
SELECT DISTINCT city, country
FROM acme_address
WHERE country = 'UNITED STATES'
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
%RESULTS[query]
{
  ds:vdp,
  ordered:no,
  type:superset
}
SELECT DISTINCT city, country
FROM all_addresses
WHERE country = 'UNITED STATES'
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
